  "hasSensitivityAnalysis": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/sensitivity/turbulence-viscosity-sa-001",
    "type": "SensitivityAnalysis",
    "name": "Sensitivity analysis — turbulence model and blood analogue viscosity",
    "description": "One-at-a-time and Morris screening sensitivity analysis varied turbulence model closure (SST k-omega vs. realizable k-epsilon vs. RSM) and blood analogue dynamic viscosity (±8% around nominal 3.5 mPa·s) across all 5 operating points. Turbulence model choice accounts for 68% of the variance in predicted NIH, driving the wide ±12% combined uncertainty bounds reported in the hemolysis validation result; viscosity uncertainty contributes a further 21%. Flow-rate predictions are comparatively insensitive (turbulence model accounts for only 9% of velocity-field variance). These findings informed the decision to accept the package at MRL 2 with documented residual bias rather than require a higher-fidelity turbulence closure."
  },
